User: Ok, I've saved the files as instructed. Git Bash started doing something and I had to close it. I've opened it back up, please walk me through all steps from fresh start, just code and as little explaination as possible. Code, expected output, check back if___, proceed if not.

Gemini: Set Terraform PATH for Git Bash:

export PATH="$PATH:/c/terraform"
Expected Result: No error message.

Set gcloud Python PATH for Git Bash:

export PATH="$PATH:/c/Program Files (x86)/Google/Cloud SDK/google-cloud-sdk/platform/bundledpython"
(Adjust path if your Python directory is different). Expected Result: No error message.

Verify gcloud is working:

gcloud --version
Expected Result: Output shows Google Cloud SDK version information. Check back if: Error messages about gcloud or Python not found. Proceed if not.

Make universal-deploy-script.sh executable (if not already done):

chmod +x universal-deploy-script.sh
Expected Result: No error message. Check back if: Error messages about chmod. Proceed if not.

Run universal-deploy-script.sh for Cloud Run deployment:

./universal-deploy-script.sh --project ai-execution-system --region us-central1 --type run
Expected Result: Script starts executing. Output will begin with "Enabling required GCP services...". Check back if: Immediate error messages before "Enabling...". Proceed if not.

After running command 6, PASTE the ENTIRE OUTPUT here. Let's see what happens with universal-deploy-script.sh.
